703690f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - 1st Place
703690f-a.text:
Clinton Street, at the N.w. corner of First Place, showing the West-
minster Presbyterian Church organised on danuary 31, 1856. It was opened
for services in a frame structure on this site in 1856. In 1867 this
building was erected. In 1929 it had become the Norwegian's Sailor Church.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
